with that every day.

00:23:46.910 --> 00:23:49.810
Now, there's no way to
absolutely deny access,

00:23:49.810 --> 00:23:50.600
obviously.

00:23:50.600 --> 00:23:54.610
You're a person living
in the modern world.

00:23:54.610 --> 00:23:56.110
And I wrestle with this.

00:23:56.110 --> 00:23:59.442
I can't go out of my apartment
without seeing billboards.

00:23:59.442 --> 00:24:01.900
And every time I see one, I
have this parenthetical message

00:24:01.900 --> 00:24:04.840
in my head-- made you look.

00:24:04.840 --> 00:24:07.720
So it's like a constant
warfare, and I really

00:24:07.720 --> 00:24:11.380
do feel like my force
fields are up all the time.

00:24:11.380 --> 00:24:13.000
It's like this
pressure, and it makes

00:24:13.000 --> 00:24:16.600
me feel like a foreigner
in my own culture.

00:24:16.600 --> 00:24:18.939
And I don't like
feeling like that.

00:24:18.939 --> 00:24:20.980
But at least I know that
that kind of advertising

00:24:20.980 --> 00:24:22.390
is relatively harmless.

00:24:22.390 --> 00:24:28.330
When you get into watching a
political debate on television,

00:24:28.330 --> 00:24:30.430
you can feel them
trying to channel you

00:24:30.430 --> 00:24:32.980
into left audience,
right audience

00:24:32.980 --> 00:24:35.560
and then trying to encourage
your brand loyalty.

00:24:35.560 --> 00:24:38.500
And that's harmful.

00:24:38.500 --> 00:24:41.260
You've seen the rise
of polarization.

00:24:41.260 --> 00:24:42.761
You've seen that
it's very difficult

00:24:42.761 --> 00:24:44.426
to have a conversation
with somebody who

00:24:44.426 --> 00:24:46.900
holds a different political
view because they immediately

00:24:46.900 --> 00:24:51.400
become defensive and hostile,
and often, so do you.

00:24:51.400 --> 00:24:55.120
So how does one deny access?

00:24:55.120 --> 00:24:59.410
Well, the simple and
obvious tools, of course--

00:24:59.410 --> 00:25:01.450
don't watch
commercial television.

00:25:01.450 --> 00:25:02.950
Watch it on Netflix.

00:25:02.950 --> 00:25:04.847
Read a book.

00:25:04.847 --> 00:25:06.430
Except I remember
one time I opened up

00:25:06.430 --> 00:25:08.430
a '70s copy of William
Goldman's "Marathon Man,"

00:25:08.430 --> 00:25:10.120
and right there
was a Marlboro ad.

00:25:10.120 --> 00:25:12.590
Great.

00:25:12.590 --> 00:25:16.060
Fortunately, that
practice is gone.

00:25:16.060 --> 00:25:21.790
Ad blockers on your computer,
using a secure browser.

00:25:21.790 --> 00:25:24.010
I, personally, use
Firefox, but I'm

00:25:24.010 --> 00:25:26.500
going to bow to the superior
experience of everybody

00:25:26.500 --> 00:25:27.310
in here.

00:25:27.310 --> 00:25:32.900
Adblock Plus is still, despite
recent issues, still very good.

00:25:32.900 --> 00:25:35.320
I'm able to watch YouTube
without commercials popping up.

00:25:35.320 --> 00:25:36.550
That's helpful.

00:25:36.550 --> 00:25:39.940
Just being aware and
finding every way

00:25:39.940 --> 00:25:43.750
you can deny access without
cutting yourself off.

00:25:43.750 --> 00:25:46.120
Yes, it requires effort,
and it requires thought,

00:25:46.120 --> 00:25:48.880
and it requires application.

00:25:48.880 --> 00:25:52.700
But it's something, I
feel, that has to be done.

00:25:52.700 --> 00:25:54.730
It's a survival
skill in our culture

00:25:54.730 --> 00:25:57.642
so that you can know that the
opinions that you've formed

00:25:57.642 --> 00:26:00.100
and the choices that you make
day to day-- economic as well

00:26:00.100 --> 00:26:01.040
as political choices.

00:26:01.040 --> 00:26:02.719
Whether you go to
Harry's Burger,

00:26:02.719 --> 00:26:04.510
where a man is his own
boss, or whether you

00:26:04.510 --> 00:26:08.460
go to McDonald's, where a
person is putting together

00:26:08.460 --> 00:26:11.335
your food by factoring rules
written by some guy in Ohio--

00:26:14.320 --> 00:26:16.540
are those choices your own?

00:26:16.540 --> 00:26:18.220
If you have the
firewall in place,

00:26:18.220 --> 00:26:20.560
and if you try to deny
access, you can at least

00:26:20.560 --> 00:26:23.780
feel a little more confident.

